Metadata: Chloriolins A-C, chlorinated sesquiterpenes produced by fungal cultures separated from a "Jaspis" marine sponge

Three novel chlorinated terpenoids were isolated from an unidentified fungus taken from the Indo-Pacific sponge "Jaspi" aff. "johnstoni". Chloriolin A, a degraded bicyclic sesquiterpene, is accompanied by the new sesquiterpenes chloriolin B and C. The previously reported tricyclic sesquiterpenes coriolin B and dihydrocoriolin C, reported from the terrestrial wood-rotting fungus "Coriolus consors", were also present in the cultures.
